cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for analyzing videos of a running event. The methods involve object detection and tracking, which are common topics in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The evaluation of the proposed methods involves measuring performance metrics, which could be considered as a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions athlete health monitoring, which could be related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.GR (Graphics).
